  "text": "There are two common approaches to deal with the multiscale problem. A standard approach is to feed the different sizes of an image into a network and then aggregate the feature maps or score maps together [CITATION_1] . This is helpful to handle the multi-scale objects and improve the segmentation accuracy. However, it usually requires a large amount of computation.",
